<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1932-08-15T15:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1932-08-15T15:00:00-05:00" n="212" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d212">
                            <note rend="inline" type="source">862.00/2821a: Telegram</note>
                            <head><hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Acting Secretary of
                                        State</gloss> to the Ambassador in Germany (<persName corresp="#p_SFM1" type="to">Sackett</persName>)</hi></head>
                            <opener>
                                <dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1932-08-15T16:00:00-04:00">August 15, 1932—4
                                        p.m.</date></dateline>
                            </opener>
                            <p>95. I hope you will find it possible to send more frequent and
                                complete telegraphic reports on the situation in Germany during
                                these critical days. What we want is not so much factual reporting
                                as an analysis of the political situation and the general trend of
                                its probable development.</p>
                            <closer><signed><persName corresp="#p_CWR1"><hi rend="smallcaps">Castle</hi></persName></signed></closer>
                        </div>
                        </body></text></TEI>